1
00:00:07,458 --> 00:00:08,792
Katara: WATER...

2
00:00:08,834 --> 00:00:11,458
EARTH...

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,458
FIRE...

4
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:15,583
AIR.

5
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:17,000
LONG AGO...

6
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:19,083
THE FOUR NATIONS LIVED
TOGETHER IN HARMONY.

7
00:00:19,125 --> 00:00:24,125
THEN EVERYTHING CHANGED
WHEN THE FIRE NATION ATTACKED.

8
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:28,041
ONLY THE AVATAR,
MASTER OF ALL FOUR ELEMENTS
COULD STOP THEM.

9
00:00:28,083 --> 00:00:29,834
BUT WHEN THE WORLD
NEEDED HIM MOST

10
00:00:29,875 --> 00:00:32,041
HE VANISHED.

11
00:00:32,083 --> 00:00:35,542
100 YEARS PASSED AND MY BROTHER
AND I DISCOVERED THE NEW AVATAR

12
00:00:35,583 --> 00:00:37,500
AN AIRBENDER NAMED AANG.

13
00:00:37,542 --> 00:00:39,917
AND ALTHOUGH HIS AIRBENDING
SKILLS WERE GREAT

14
00:00:39,959 --> 00:00:43,125
HE HAS A LOT TO LEARN BEFORE
HE'S READY TO SAVE ANYONE.

15
00:00:43,166 --> 00:00:47,125
BUT I BELIEVE AANG
CAN SAVE THE WORLD.

16
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:49,333
♪

17
00:00:55,542 --> 00:00:58,750
Ozai: I AM PROUD OF YOU,
PRINCE ZUKO.

18
00:00:58,792 --> 00:01:01,625
I AM PROUD BECAUSE WHEN YOUR
LOYALTY WAS TESTED

19
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:03,625
BY YOUR TREACHEROUS UNCLE

20
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:05,125
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING

21
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:06,959
AND CAPTURED THE TRAITOR.

22
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,417
Zuko: WHY DID YOU TELL FATHER
THAT I WAS THE ONE
WHO KILLED THE AVATAR?

23
00:01:10,458 --> 00:01:11,542
PLEASE, ZUKO...

24
00:01:11,583 --> 00:01:14,542
WHAT ULTERIOR MOTIVE
COULD I HAVE

25
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:19,000
UNLESS SOMEHOW THE AVATAR
WAS ACTUALLY ALIVE?

26
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:21,875
ALL THAT GLORY WOULD
SUDDENLY TURN TO SHAME.

27
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:26,208
♪

28
00:02:03,542 --> 00:02:05,166
WHO'S THERE?

29
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:17,166
[WIND HOWLING]

30
00:02:17,208 --> 00:02:20,250
Aang: I THINK I SEE
A CAVE BELOW.

31
00:02:20,291 --> 00:02:22,667
Sokka: SHH... KEEP QUIET.

32
00:02:25,291 --> 00:02:27,041
[BIRD SQUAWKS]

33
00:02:27,083 --> 00:02:28,500
[APPA GRUNTS]

34
00:02:28,542 --> 00:02:32,208
GREAT JOB WITH THE CLOUD CAMO,
BUT NEXT TIME...

35
00:02:32,250 --> 00:02:36,500
LET'S DISGUISE OURSELVES
AS THE KIND OF CLOUD WHO KNOWS
HOW TO KEEP ITS MOUTH SHUT.

36
00:02:36,542 --> 00:02:39,458
Toph: YEAH, WE WOULDN'T WANT
A BIRD TO HEAR US CHATTING UP
THERE AND TURN US IN.

37
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,166
HEY, WE'RE IN ENEMY TERRITORY.

38
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:44,709
THOSE ARE ENEMY BIRDS.

39
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:46,917
[SQUAWK]

40
00:02:46,959 --> 00:02:48,583
[CHUCKLING]

41
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:54,417
[CRASHES]

42
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:02,166
Sokka: WELL, THIS IS IT.

43
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:04,500
THIS IS HOW WE'LL BE LIVING
UNTIL THE INVASION BEGINS.

44
00:03:04,542 --> 00:03:07,166
HIDING IN CAVE AFTER CAVE...

45
00:03:07,208 --> 00:03:10,083
AFTER CAVE AFTER CAVE...

46
00:03:10,125 --> 00:03:13,291
SOKKA, WE DON'T NEED
TO BECOME CAVE PEOPLE.

47
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:15,375
WHAT WE NEED
IS SOME NEW CLOTHES.

48
00:03:15,417 --> 00:03:18,041
YEAH, BLENDING IN
IS BETTER THAN HIDING OUT.

49
00:03:18,083 --> 00:03:19,834
IF WE GET FIRE NATION DISGUISES

50
00:03:19,875 --> 00:03:23,250
WE'LL BE JUST AS SAFE AS WE
WOULD BE HIDING IN A CAVE.

51
00:03:23,291 --> 00:03:25,000
PLUS, THEY HAVE
REAL FOOD OUT THERE.

52
00:03:25,041 --> 00:03:27,208
DOES ANYONE WANNA SIT IN THE
DIRT AND EAT CAVE-HOPPERS?

53
00:03:32,667 --> 00:03:35,125
[CRUNCHING]

54
00:03:35,166 --> 00:03:38,166
LOOKS LIKE WE
GOT OUTVOTED, SPORT.

55
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:39,667
LET'S GET SOME NEW CLOTHES.

56
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:43,709
Aang: I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THIS.

57
00:03:43,750 --> 00:03:45,333
THESE CLOTHES
BELONG TO SOMEBODY.

58
00:03:45,375 --> 00:03:47,917
I CALL THE SILK ROBE.

59
00:03:50,375 --> 00:03:52,834
BUT IF IT'S ESSENTIAL
TO OUR SURVIVAL

60
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:55,041
THEN I CALL THE SUIT.

61
00:04:08,291 --> 00:04:10,166
TA-DAH... NORMAL KID.

62
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:13,458
HMM... I SHOULD
PROBABLY WEAR SHOES

63
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:16,166
BUT THEN I WON'T
BE ABLE TO SEE AS WELL.

64
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,041
SORRY SHOES...

65
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:25,166
FINALLY, A STYLISH SHOE
FOR THE BLIND EARTHBENDER.

66
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:26,583
HOW DO I LOOK?

67
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:33,041
UH, YOUR MOM'S NECKLACE.

68
00:04:33,083 --> 00:04:35,917
OH... OH, YEAH.

69
00:04:35,959 --> 00:04:38,291
I GUESS IT'S PRETTY OBVIOUSLY
WATER TRIBE, ISN'T IT?

70
00:04:51,917 --> 00:04:53,166
[MOMO PURRS]

71
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:58,792
I USED TO VISIT MY FRIEND
KUZON HERE 100 YEARS AGO.

72
00:04:58,834 --> 00:05:01,542
SO EVERYONE JUST FOLLOW
MY LEAD AND STAY COOL.

73
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:03,458
OR AS THEY SAY
IN THE FIRE NATION

74
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:06,583
"STAY FLAMIN'".

75
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:09,250
GREETINGS, MY GOOD HOTMAN.

76
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:11,166
OH, HI...

77
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:13,625
I GUESS?

78
00:05:13,667 --> 00:05:15,667
Aang: OH, WE'RE GOING
TO A MEAT PLACE?

79
00:05:15,709 --> 00:05:19,041
Sokka: COME ON, AANG,
EVERYONE HERE EATS MEAT...

80
00:05:19,083 --> 00:05:20,041
EVEN THE MEAT.

81
00:05:20,083 --> 00:05:22,250
[GROWLS]

82
00:05:22,291 --> 00:05:23,709
YOU GUYS GO AHEAD.

83
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:25,875
I'LL JUST GET SOME LETTUCE
OUT OF THE GARBAGE.

84
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:32,375
Aang: HOTMAN, HOTMAN.

85
00:05:32,417 --> 00:05:34,291
HOTMAN.

86
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,041
HOTMAN, HOTMAN.

87
00:05:37,625 --> 00:05:38,792
IT'S OVER,
WE CAUGHT YOU.

88
00:05:38,834 --> 00:05:40,500
WHO ME?

89
00:05:40,542 --> 00:05:42,750
IT COULDN'T BE MORE OBVIOUS
THAT YOU DON'T BELONG HERE.

90
00:05:43,875 --> 00:05:45,333
NEXT TIME YOU PLAY HOOKY

91
00:05:45,375 --> 00:05:48,083
YOU MIGHT WANT TO TAKE OFF
YOUR SCHOOL UNIFORM.

92
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:50,583
[NERVOUS CHUCKLE]... AH!

93
00:06:00,041 --> 00:06:01,291
OH...

94
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:03,959
Teacher: IS THIS A NEW MIND
READY FOR MOLDING?

95
00:06:04,875 --> 00:06:05,542
THAT'S RIGHT.

96
00:06:05,583 --> 00:06:07,333
LET THE MOLDING BEGIN.

97
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:08,542
Teacher: WAIT A MINUTE.

98
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:11,083
[GASPS]: YOU'RE NOT
FROM THE FIRE NATION.

99
00:06:13,458 --> 00:06:16,583
CLEARLY YOU'RE
FROM THE COLONIES.

100
00:06:17,041 --> 00:06:19,500
YEAH, THE COLONIES,
OF COURSE.

101
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:22,000
THE FIRE NATION COLONIES
IN THE EARTH KINGDOM.

102
00:06:22,625 --> 00:06:24,583
YOUR ETIQUETTE
IS TERRIBLE.

103
00:06:25,041 --> 00:06:27,166
IN THE HOMELAND,
WE BOW TO OUR ELDERS...

104
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:30,959
LIKE SO.

105
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,250
SORRY MA'AM.

106
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:41,291
AND WE DON'T WEAR
HEAD COVERINGS INDOORS.

107
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,000
UM, I HAVE A SCAR.

108
00:06:43,041 --> 00:06:44,959
IT'S REALLY EMBARRASSING.

109
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,959
VERY WELL.

110
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,000
WHAT IS YOUR NAME?

111
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:51,709
OR SHOULD WE JUST CALL YOU
MANNERLESS COLONY SLOB?

112
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:52,959
[CHUCKLES]

113
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,542
JUST "SLOB" IS FINE.

114
00:06:54,583 --> 00:06:56,500
OR, UH... KUZON.

115
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:02,375
[BELL TOLLS]

116
00:07:02,417 --> 00:07:06,583
[STUDENTS TALKING]

117
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,458
[MOMO PURRS]

118
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,208
WE MADE IT THROUGH
THE DAY, MOMO...

119
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:13,500
AND IT WAS PRETTY FUN.

120
00:07:13,542 --> 00:07:14,917
[PURRS]

121
00:07:14,959 --> 00:07:16,417
DON'T LET THE HEADMASTER
CATCH YOU WITH THAT MONKEY.

122
00:07:16,458 --> 00:07:17,750
WHAT MONKEY?

123
00:07:17,792 --> 00:07:19,542
DON'T WORRY,
I'M NOT A TATTLETALE.

124
00:07:19,583 --> 00:07:20,917
MY NAME'S ON JI.

125
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:22,875
I LIKE YOUR HEADBAND,
BY THE WAY.

126
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:27,667
ON JI, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO BABY-SIT THE NEW KID.

127
00:07:27,709 --> 00:07:29,250
WOW.

128
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:31,959
YOU MUST BE ONE OF THOSE POPULAR
KIDS I'VE BEEN HEARING ABOUT.

129
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,208
THAT'S RIGHT.

130
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:34,417
NOW LISTEN, FRIEND...

131
00:07:34,458 --> 00:07:36,041
I KNOW YOU'RE FROM THE COLONIES

132
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:37,583
SO I'LL SAY THIS SLOWLY.

133
00:07:37,625 --> 00:07:40,875
ON JI IS MY GIRLFRIEND.

134
00:07:40,917 --> 00:07:42,750
DON'T FORGET IT.

135
00:07:49,458 --> 00:07:51,125
IT WAS NICE MEETING YOU.

136
00:07:51,166 --> 00:07:52,375
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

137
00:07:52,417 --> 00:07:53,375
HE DIDN'T BEAT YOU UP.

138
00:07:53,417 --> 00:07:54,750
NOT EVEN A LITTLE.

139
00:07:54,792 --> 00:07:56,208
I GUESS I'M JUST LUCKY.

140
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:58,583
WE WERE ON OUR WAY TO PLAY
HIDE AND EXPLODE.

141
00:07:58,625 --> 00:07:59,542
YOU WANNA COME?

142
00:07:59,583 --> 00:08:01,166
I'D LOVE TO.

143
00:08:06,792 --> 00:08:08,959
Katara: WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

144
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,375
WE'VE BEEN WORRIED SICK.

145
00:08:10,417 --> 00:08:12,375
I GOT INVITED TO PLAY
WITH SOME KIDS AFTER SCHOOL.

146
00:08:14,542 --> 00:08:15,917
Sokka: AFTER WHAT?

147
00:08:15,959 --> 00:08:17,750
I ENROLLED IN
A FIRE NATION SCHOOL

148
00:08:17,792 --> 00:08:19,000
AND I'M GOING BACK TOMORROW.

149
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:21,375
ENROLLED IN WHAT?

150
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:32,291
YOU AGAIN?

151
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:34,625
STOP WHERE YOU ARE.

152
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:37,041
Guard: PRINCE ZUKO?

153
00:08:37,083 --> 00:08:37,875
[SWORD CLANKS]

154
00:08:37,917 --> 00:08:39,375
AH!

155
00:08:39,417 --> 00:08:40,917
I'M GOING IN FOR A VISIT.

156
00:08:40,959 --> 00:08:42,625
YOU'RE GONNA STAND GUARD HERE

157
00:08:42,667 --> 00:08:45,875
AND NO ONE IS GOING
TO KNOW ABOUT THIS.

158
00:08:54,417 --> 00:08:55,458
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

159
00:08:58,458 --> 00:09:01,417
UNCLE... IT'S ME.

160
00:09:11,834 --> 00:09:15,583
AANG, I'M TRYING TO
BE MATURE AND NOT IMMEDIATELY
SHOOT DOWN YOUR IDEA.

161
00:09:15,625 --> 00:09:18,250
BUT IT SOUNDS...
REALLY TERRIBLE.

162
00:09:18,291 --> 00:09:20,250
YEAH, WE GOT OUR OUTFITS.

163
00:09:20,291 --> 00:09:22,542
WHAT DO YOU NEED
TO GO TO SCHOOL FOR?

164
00:09:22,583 --> 00:09:24,542
EVERY MINUTE
I'M IN THAT CLASSROOM

165
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:27,458
I'M LEARNING NEW THINGS
ABOUT THE FIRE NATION.

166
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,709
I ALREADY HAVE A PICTURE
OF FIRE LORD, OZAI.

167
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:31,458
AND HERE'S ONE THAT
I MADE OUT OF NOODLES.

168
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,709
IMPRESSIVE, I ADMIT.

169
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:35,375
BUT I STILL THINK
IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.

170
00:09:35,417 --> 00:09:39,250
I GUESS WE'LL NEVER FIND OUT
ABOUT THE SECRET RIVER, THEN.

171
00:09:39,291 --> 00:09:42,250
IT GOES RIGHT TO
THE FIRE LORD'S PALACE.

172
00:09:42,291 --> 00:09:45,250
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO LEARN
ABOUT IT IN CLASS TOMORROW...

173
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:49,667
HMM... I AM A FAN
OF SECRET RIVERS.

174
00:09:49,709 --> 00:09:52,500
FINE, LET'S STAY
A FEW MORE DAYS.

175
00:09:52,542 --> 00:09:54,417
FLAMEY-O, HOTMAN.

176
00:09:56,667 --> 00:09:59,500
FLAMEY-O?
[SHRUGS] UM-UM.

177
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,583
Zuko: YOU BROUGHT THIS
ON YOURSELF, YOU KNOW.

178
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:05,333
WE COULD HAVE RETURNED TOGETHER.

179
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:07,000
YOU COULD HAVE BEEN A HERO.

180
00:10:08,792 --> 00:10:10,917
YOU HAD NO RIGHT
TO JUDGE ME, UNCLE.

181
00:10:10,959 --> 00:10:13,875
I DID WHAT I HAD TO DO
IN BA SING SE

182
00:10:13,917 --> 00:10:15,166
AND YOU'RE A FOOL
FOR NOT JOINING ME.

183
00:10:17,458 --> 00:10:21,125
YOU'RE NOT
GONNA SAY ANYTHING?

184
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:22,291
OH!

185
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:24,041
[YELLS]

186
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:26,208
YOU'RE A CRAZY OLD MAN.

187
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:28,291
YOU'RE CRAZY,
AND IF YOU WEREN'T IN JAIL

188
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:30,709
YOU'D BE SLEEPING
IN A GUTTER.

189
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:38,333
Teacher: GOOD MORNING, CLASS.

190
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,083
RECITE THE FIRE NATION OATH.

191
00:10:42,667 --> 00:10:45,166
Students: MY LIFE,
I GIVE TO MY COUNTRY.

192
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:46,625
WITH MY HANDS,
I FIGHT FOR FIRE LORD...

193
00:10:46,667 --> 00:10:48,417
Aang: FIRE LORD...

194
00:10:48,458 --> 00:10:50,083
FOREFATHERS...

195
00:10:50,125 --> 00:10:52,458
Students: WITH MY MIND, I SEEK
WAYS TO BETTER MY COUNTRY

196
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:54,125
AND WITH MY FEET...

197
00:10:54,166 --> 00:10:55,166
Aang: FIREBENDERS...

198
00:10:55,208 --> 00:10:56,875
FIRE LORD.

199
00:10:56,917 --> 00:10:59,542
WHA, BAH,
BLAH, BLAH.
[STUDENTS CHUCKLING]

200
00:11:04,917 --> 00:11:08,291
SINCE IT'S OBVIOUSLY HILARIOUS
TO MOCK OUR NATIONAL OATH

201
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:11,250
WE'LL BEGIN WITH A POP QUIZ ON
OUR GREAT MARCH OF CIVILIZATION.

202
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:14,083
[STUDENTS GROAN]

203
00:11:14,125 --> 00:11:16,250
Teacher: QUESTION ONE.

204
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:19,083
WHAT YEAR DID FIRE LORD SOZIN
BATTLE THE AIR NATION ARMY?

205
00:11:21,875 --> 00:11:23,417
KUZON?

206
00:11:23,458 --> 00:11:25,417
Aang: IS THAT A TRICK QUESTION?

207
00:11:25,458 --> 00:11:28,583
THE AIR NOMADS DIDN'T
HAVE A FORMAL MILITARY.

208
00:11:28,625 --> 00:11:32,750
SOZIN DEFEATED THEM BY AMBUSH.

209
00:11:32,792 --> 00:11:36,667
Teacher: WELL, I DON'T KNOW HOW
<i>YOU</i> COULD POSSIBLY KNOW MORE
THAN OUR NATIONAL HISTORY BOOK

210
00:11:36,709 --> 00:11:39,417
UNLESS YOU WERE THERE
A HUNDRED YEARS AGO.

211
00:11:39,458 --> 00:11:41,041
I'LL JUST WRITE DOWN
MY BEST GUESS.

212
00:11:46,208 --> 00:11:49,125
[ORCHESTRA PLAYS]

213
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:52,458
[PLAYS WRONG NOTES]

214
00:11:54,333 --> 00:11:55,709
Music Teacher: KUZON?

215
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:56,834
[STOPS PLAYING]

216
00:11:56,875 --> 00:12:00,834
I KNOW, I'M A TERRIBLE
TSUNGI HORNIST.

217
00:12:00,875 --> 00:12:02,000
NO, CHILD.

218
00:12:02,041 --> 00:12:03,917
THAT HULLABALOO GOING
ON WITH YOUR FEET.

219
00:12:03,959 --> 00:12:06,041
IS THAT A NERVOUS DISORDER?

220
00:12:06,083 --> 00:12:08,625
I WAS JUST DANCING.

221
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:11,083
YOU DO DANCES HERE IN THE
HOMELAND, RIGHT?

222
00:12:11,125 --> 00:12:13,166
NOT REALLY, NO.

223
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:17,000
DANCING IS NOT CONDUCIVE TO
A PROPER LEARNING ENVIRONMENT.

224
00:12:17,041 --> 00:12:20,000
YOUNG PEOPLE MUST HAVE RIGID
DISCIPLINE AND ORDER.

225
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:21,959
Aang: BUT WHAT ABOUT
EXPRESSING YOURSELF?

226
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:25,041
I KNOW SOMETIMES WE'RE SO MOVED
BY OUR LOVE FOR OUR NATION

227
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:28,917
THAT WE CAN'T CONTROL
OUR OWN BODIES.

228
00:12:28,959 --> 00:12:30,792
IF YOU MUST

229
00:12:30,834 --> 00:12:35,542
YOU MAY MARCH IN PLACE QUIETLY
NEXT TIME THE URGE HITS YOU.

230
00:12:35,583 --> 00:12:38,417
[MUSIC RESUMES]

231
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:51,625
[ALL TALKING/WHISPERING]

232
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:53,000
OH, HI, KUZON.

233
00:12:53,041 --> 00:12:55,583
I REALLY LIKED THAT CRAZY
DANCE YOU WERE DOING.

234
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:56,750
THANKS, ON JI.

235
00:12:56,792 --> 00:12:58,500
I COULD SHOW IT TO YOU
AGAIN IF YOU'D LIKE.

236
00:12:58,542 --> 00:12:59,458
AH!

237
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:01,458
WHAT'D YOU SAY,
COLONY TRASH?

238
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:03,166
YOU'RE GONNA SHOW HER SOMETHING?

239
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:04,875
JUST SOME
DANCE MOVEMENTS.

240
00:13:04,917 --> 00:13:06,875
NOBODY SHOWS
MY ON JI ANYTHING

241
00:13:06,917 --> 00:13:08,792
ESPECIALLY MOVEMENT.

242
00:13:08,834 --> 00:13:09,792
[GRUNTS]

243
00:13:11,959 --> 00:13:13,709
[GRUNTS]

244
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:16,250
[AUDIBLE STRUGGLING...]

245
00:13:20,709 --> 00:13:21,375
AH!

246
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:24,500
HA!

247
00:13:25,291 --> 00:13:26,250
YAH!

248
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:27,375
AH.

249
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,375
[GRUNTS]

250
00:13:34,875 --> 00:13:38,000
[SNIFFLES]

251
00:13:38,041 --> 00:13:40,875
PICKING FIGHTS
ON YOUR SECOND DAY?

252
00:13:40,917 --> 00:13:43,291
WE NEED TO HAVE A CONFERENCE
TO DISCUSS YOUR PUNISHMENT.

253
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,041
BRING YOUR PARENTS
TO MY OFFICE AFTER SCHOOL.

254
00:13:45,083 --> 00:13:46,917
PARENTS, BUT...

255
00:13:46,959 --> 00:13:48,083
DON'T BE LATE.

256
00:13:57,709 --> 00:13:59,917
THANK YOU FOR COMING

257
00:13:59,959 --> 00:14:00,959
MR. AND MRS...

258
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,417
FIRE... WANG FIRE.

259
00:14:03,458 --> 00:14:06,166
THIS IS MY WIFE,
SAPPHIRE.

260
00:14:06,208 --> 00:14:07,917
SAPPHIRE FIRE,
NICE TO MEET YOU.

261
00:14:07,959 --> 00:14:10,542
MR. AND MRS. FIRE...

262
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:13,000
YOUR SON HAS BEEN ENROLLED
HERE FOR TWO DAYS

263
00:14:13,041 --> 00:14:14,917
AND HE'S ALREADY
CAUSING PROBLEMS.

264
00:14:14,959 --> 00:14:16,083
HE'S ARGUED WITH
HIS HISTORY TEACHER

265
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:18,125
DISRUPTED MUSIC CLASS

266
00:14:18,166 --> 00:14:19,917
AND ROUGHED UP MY STAR PUPIL.

267
00:14:19,959 --> 00:14:21,500
MY GOODNESS.

268
00:14:21,542 --> 00:14:23,125
THAT DOESN'T SOUND
LIKE OUR KUZON.

269
00:14:23,166 --> 00:14:25,000
THAT'S WHAT ANY MOTHER
WOULD SAY, MA'AM.

270
00:14:25,041 --> 00:14:27,000
NONETHELESS,
YOU'RE FOREWARNED.

271
00:14:27,041 --> 00:14:29,041
IF HE ACTS UP
ONE MORE TIME

272
00:14:29,083 --> 00:14:31,166
I'LL HAVE HIM SENT
TO REFORM SCHOOL...

273
00:14:31,208 --> 00:14:33,917
BY WHICH I MEAN THE COAL MINES.

274
00:14:33,959 --> 00:14:35,083
ARE WE CLEAR?

275
00:14:35,125 --> 00:14:37,417
DON'T YOU WORRY,
MR. HEADMASTER

276
00:14:37,458 --> 00:14:40,417
I'LL STRAIGHTEN THIS BOY
OUT SOMETHING FIERCE.

277
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:43,875
YOUNG MAN, AS SON AS WE GET
HOME, YOU'RE GONNA GET THE
PUNISHMENT OF A LIFETIME.

278
00:14:43,917 --> 00:14:46,291
THAT'S WHAT I LIKE TO HEAR.

279
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,583
Mai: ORANGE IS SUCH
AN AWFUL COLOR.

280
00:14:54,625 --> 00:14:56,542
[SNICKERS]

281
00:14:56,583 --> 00:14:58,959
YOU'RE SO BEAUTIFUL
WHEN YOU HATE THE WORLD.

282
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,959
I DON'T HATE YOU.

283
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:03,041
I DON'T HATE YOU, TOO.

284
00:15:03,083 --> 00:15:05,083
[AZULA CLEARS THROAT]

285
00:15:05,125 --> 00:15:07,875
ZUKO, COULD I HAVE
A WORD WITH YOU?

286
00:15:07,917 --> 00:15:10,834
CAN'T YOU SEE WE'RE BUSY?

287
00:15:10,875 --> 00:15:15,583
OH, MAI, TY LEE NEEDS YOUR HELP
UNTANGLING HER BRAID.

288
00:15:15,625 --> 00:15:17,917
SOUNDS PRETTY SERIOUS.

289
00:15:23,667 --> 00:15:27,667
SO I HEAR YOU'VE BEEN
TO VISIT YOUR UNCLE FATSO
IN THE PRISON TOWER.

290
00:15:27,709 --> 00:15:29,875
THAT GUARD TOLD YOU.

291
00:15:29,917 --> 00:15:32,917
NO, YOU DID... JUST NOW.

292
00:15:32,959 --> 00:15:35,917
OK, YOU CAUGHT ME.

293
00:15:35,959 --> 00:15:37,792
WHAT IS IT THAT
YOU WANT, AZULA.

294
00:15:37,834 --> 00:15:40,208
ACTUALLY, NOTHING.

295
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:43,291
BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
I'M LOOKING OUT FOR YOU.

296
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:45,208
IF PEOPLE FIND OUT
YOU'VE BEEN TO SEE UNCLE

297
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:47,834
THEY'LL THINK YOU'RE
PLOTTING WITH HIM.

298
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:51,250
JUST BE CAREFUL DUM-DUM.

299
00:15:53,583 --> 00:15:55,667
[BIRDS SQUAWK]

300
00:15:55,709 --> 00:15:56,834
THAT SETTLES IT.

301
00:15:56,875 --> 00:15:58,500
NO MORE SCHOOL FOR YOU,
YOUNG MAN.

302
00:15:58,542 --> 00:16:00,250
Aang: I'M NOT
READY TO LEAVE.

303
00:16:00,291 --> 00:16:01,792
I'M HAVING FUN FOR ONCE

304
00:16:01,834 --> 00:16:04,000
JUST BEING A NORMAL KID.

305
00:16:04,041 --> 00:16:06,125
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S LIKE, SOKKA.

306
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:07,750
YOU GET TO BE NORMAL
ALL THE TIME.

307
00:16:07,792 --> 00:16:10,083
HA, HA.

308
00:16:10,125 --> 00:16:13,417
LISTEN, GUYS, THOSE KIDS
AT SCHOOL ARE THE FUTURE
OF THE FIRE NATION.

309
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:15,583
IF WE WANNA CHANGE
THIS PLACE FOR THE BETTER

310
00:16:15,625 --> 00:16:18,041
WE NEED TO SHOW THEM
A LITTLE TASTE OF FREEDOM.

311
00:16:18,083 --> 00:16:22,250
WHAT COULD YOU POSSIBLY DO
FOR A COUNTRY OF DEPRAVED
LITTLE FIRE MONSTERS?

312
00:16:22,291 --> 00:16:25,000
I'M GONNA THROW THEM
A SECRET DANCE PARTY.

313
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:27,417
GO TO YOUR ROOM.

314
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:39,709
I CAN'T BELIEVE WE'RE
HAVING A DANCE PARTY.

315
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:41,583
IT SEEMS SO... SILLY.

316
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:43,834
DON'T THINK OF IT
AS A DANCE PARTY

317
00:16:43,875 --> 00:16:47,083
BUT AS A CULTURAL EVENT
CELEBRATING THE ART
OF FANCY FOOTWORK.

318
00:16:49,583 --> 00:16:50,667
THEY'RE COMING.

319
00:16:50,709 --> 00:16:52,709
EVERYONE STOP BENDING.

320
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,792
Aang: SORRY, BUDDY.

321
00:16:54,834 --> 00:16:57,166
YOU SHOULD PROBABLY
WAIT OUT BACK.

322
00:16:57,208 --> 00:16:59,333
[GROWLS]

323
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:02,458
Aang: I KNOW, YOU'VE GOT
FANCIER FEET THAN ANYBODY...

324
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:04,041
AND SIX OF 'EM.

325
00:17:08,291 --> 00:17:10,667
[MUSIC PLAYS]

326
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:15,125
Aang: LADIES AND GENTLEMEN.

327
00:17:15,166 --> 00:17:17,792
THE FLAMEY-Os!

328
00:17:17,834 --> 00:17:20,959
YEAH, THIS OUGHT TO GET
EVERYBODY MOVING.

329
00:17:23,709 --> 00:17:26,417
NOW WHAT
DO WE DO?

330
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:28,375
THIS IS WHEN YOU START DANCING.

331
00:17:28,417 --> 00:17:31,792
I DON'T THINK
MY PARENTS WANT ME
DANCING IN A CAVE.

332
00:17:31,834 --> 00:17:35,959
YEAH, WHAT IF SOMEONE
FINDS OUT?

333
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:36,625
OH, BOY.

334
00:17:36,667 --> 00:17:38,000
LISTEN, GUYS...

335
00:17:38,041 --> 00:17:40,000
DANCING ISN'T SOMETHING
YOU THINK ABOUT.

336
00:17:40,041 --> 00:17:41,583
IT'S A FORM OF SELF-EXPRESSION

337
00:17:41,625 --> 00:17:44,166
THAT NO ONE CAN EVER
TAKE AWAY FROM YOU.

338
00:17:44,208 --> 00:17:47,875
MAYBE IT WAS DIFFERENT
IN THE COLONIES, KUZON,
BUT WE DON'T DO THAT HERE.

339
00:17:47,917 --> 00:17:48,917
SURE YOU DO.

340
00:17:48,959 --> 00:17:51,166
YOU HAVE FOR GENERATIONS.

341
00:17:51,208 --> 00:17:54,041
IT JUST SO HAPPENS
THAT I KNOW SEVERAL CLASSIC
FIRE NATION DANCES.

342
00:17:54,083 --> 00:17:56,250
A HUNDRED YEARS AGO

343
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:57,792
THIS WAS KNOWN AS
"THE PHOENIX FLIGHT."

344
00:17:57,834 --> 00:18:00,041
Students: OOH... WOW.

345
00:18:00,083 --> 00:18:03,083
AND THIS WAS
THE "CAMELEPHANT STRUT".

346
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:07,875
[GIGGLING]

347
00:18:10,208 --> 00:18:11,417
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

348
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:14,875
WHO KNEW TWINKLE TOES
COULD DANCE?

349
00:18:14,917 --> 00:18:16,291
[CHEERING CONTINUES]

350
00:18:18,125 --> 00:18:20,625
I BROUGHT YOU SOME
KOMODO-CHICKEN.

351
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:22,333
I KNOW YOU DON'T CARE FOR IT

352
00:18:22,375 --> 00:18:24,709
BUT I FIGURE
IT BEATS PRISON FOOD.

353
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:25,959
I ADMIT IT.

354
00:18:26,041 --> 00:18:28,333
I HAVE EVERYTHING
I ALWAYS WANTED

355
00:18:28,375 --> 00:18:32,959
BUT IT'S NOT AT ALL HOW
I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE.

356
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,041
THE TRUTH IS I NEED YOUR ADVICE.

357
00:18:36,083 --> 00:18:39,166
I THINK THE AVATAR
IS STILL ALIVE.

358
00:18:39,208 --> 00:18:41,125
I KNOW HE'S OUT THERE.

359
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:43,959
I'M LOSING MY MIND.

360
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,834
PLEASE, UNCLE, I'M SO CONFUSED,
I NEED YOUR HELP.

361
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:50,667
FORGET IT.

362
00:18:50,709 --> 00:18:51,792
I'LL SOLVE THIS MYSELF.

363
00:18:51,834 --> 00:18:53,750
WASTE AWAY IN HERE
FOR ALL I CARE.

364
00:18:58,458 --> 00:19:00,542
[DOOR CREAKS SHUT]

365
00:19:04,834 --> 00:19:07,750
[DANCE MUSIC CONTINUES]

366
00:19:07,792 --> 00:19:10,834
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

367
00:19:13,291 --> 00:19:15,709
AND THIS IS HOW THEY DO IT IN
THE BALLROOMS OF BA SING SE.

368
00:19:21,542 --> 00:19:23,625
WOW, THEY LOOK PRETTY
GOOD TOGETHER.

369
00:19:23,667 --> 00:19:26,083
EH, IF THAT'S WHAT YOU LIKE.

370
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:29,375
Aang: YEAH, THAT'S IT.

371
00:19:29,417 --> 00:19:32,041
THAT'S THE SOUND OF HAPPY FEET.

372
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:38,250
ALL RIGHT, GO WITH THAT.

373
00:19:38,291 --> 00:19:39,750
EVERYBODY, FREESTYLE.

374
00:19:57,375 --> 00:19:58,917
I DON'T KNOW, AANG.

375
00:19:58,959 --> 00:20:00,875
THESE SHOES AREN'T
REALLY RIGHT FOR DANCING

376
00:20:00,917 --> 00:20:03,208
AND I'M NOT SURE
THAT I KNOW HOW TO...

377
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:04,000
TAKE MY HAND.

378
00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:05,417
OK.

379
00:20:26,709 --> 00:20:28,625
AANG, EVERYONE'S WATCHING.

380
00:20:28,667 --> 00:20:30,208
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THEM.

381
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:32,750
IT'S JUST YOU AND ME RIGHT NOW.

382
00:20:57,417 --> 00:20:59,083
[STUDENTS GASP]

383
00:20:59,125 --> 00:21:00,834
Student: WOW.

384
00:21:10,792 --> 00:21:12,125
[MUSIC ENDS]
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

385
00:21:12,166 --> 00:21:14,959
[PANTING]

386
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,250
[FAINT CHEERING]

387
00:21:17,291 --> 00:21:19,959
IT<i> IS</i> A DANCING PARTY.

388
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,417
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING BY
TELLING ME, HIDE.

389
00:21:22,458 --> 00:21:23,709
ANYTIME,
HEADMASTER, SIR.

390
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:27,500
THIS IS INCREDIBLE.

391
00:21:27,542 --> 00:21:29,458
IT'S LIKE MY INHIBITIONS
JUST DISAPPEAR.

392
00:21:34,625 --> 00:21:37,792
OK, THEY'RE BACK AGAIN.

393
00:21:37,834 --> 00:21:39,000
Headmaster: HE'S
THE ONE WE WANT.

394
00:21:39,291 --> 00:21:42,000
THE BOY WITH THE HEADBAND.

395
00:21:42,041 --> 00:21:42,959
UH-OH.

396
00:21:48,834 --> 00:21:49,875
Guard: GOT YA.

397
00:21:49,917 --> 00:21:50,875
LOOKING FOR ME?

398
00:21:52,542 --> 00:21:54,250
THAT'S NOT THE ONE.

399
00:21:54,291 --> 00:21:55,709
HE'S HERE SOMEWHERE.

400
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:57,000
DON'T LET HIM LEAVE THE CAVE.

401
00:22:02,083 --> 00:22:02,792
YES?

402
00:22:07,834 --> 00:22:09,458
HI THERE.
HOW WE DOING?

403
00:22:16,959 --> 00:22:18,125
LOOKING FOR SOMEONE?

404
00:22:19,750 --> 00:22:21,000
WHO ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR?

405
00:22:21,041 --> 00:22:22,667
DO YOU NEED SOMETHING?

406
00:22:22,709 --> 00:22:23,375
OVER HERE.

407
00:22:37,041 --> 00:22:40,041
STOP THAT.

408
00:22:40,083 --> 00:22:41,333
STOP THAT.

409
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,792
WE'RE SAFE, SOKKA.

410
00:22:45,834 --> 00:22:47,542
YOU CAN TAKE OFF
THE MOUSTACHE, NOW.

411
00:22:47,583 --> 00:22:49,166
OH, NO, I CAN'T.

412
00:22:49,208 --> 00:22:52,000
IT'S PERMANENTLY
GLUED TO MY SKIN.

413
00:22:52,041 --> 00:22:54,083
WAY TO GO, DANCY PANTS.

414
00:22:54,125 --> 00:22:56,375
I THINK YOU REALLY
DID HELP THOSE KIDS.

415
00:22:56,417 --> 00:22:58,291
YOU TAUGHT THEM TO BE FREE.

416
00:22:58,333 --> 00:22:59,333
I DON'T KNOW.

417
00:22:59,375 --> 00:23:01,458
IT WAS JUST
A DANCE PARTY, THAT'S ALL.

418
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:04,125
WELL, THAT WAS SOME
DANCE PARTY, AANG.

419
00:23:04,166 --> 00:23:05,542
MWAH.

420
00:23:07,083 --> 00:23:08,709
FLAMEY-O, SIR...

421
00:23:08,750 --> 00:23:10,458
FLAMEY-O.

422
00:23:15,917 --> 00:23:18,792
[BIRDS CAWING]

423
00:23:20,875 --> 00:23:22,250
[GATE OPENS]

424
00:23:24,083 --> 00:23:26,208
YOU'RE SURE
YOU WEREN'T FOLLOWED?

425
00:23:26,250 --> 00:23:28,250
Zuko: I'VE HEARD ABOUT YOU.

426
00:23:28,291 --> 00:23:30,166
THEY SAY YOU'RE GOOD
AT WHAT YOU DO

427
00:23:30,208 --> 00:23:32,917
AND EVEN BETTER
AT KEEPING SECRETS.

428
00:23:32,959 --> 00:23:35,333
THE AVATAR'S ALIVE.

429
00:23:35,375 --> 00:23:37,375
I WANT YOU TO FIND HIM

430
00:23:37,417 --> 00:23:39,333
AND END HIM.

431
00:23:53,667 --> 00:23:57,583
♪
